casebody.data:
PEOPLE of the State of Michigan, Plaintiff-Appellee,
v.
Willie George TINSLEY, Defendant-Appellant. SC: 155837
COA: 335752 Supreme Court of Michigan. April 3, 2018

Order

On order of the Court, the application for leave to appeal the March 29, 2017 order of the Court of Appeals is considered, and it is DENIED, because the defendant has failed to meet the burden of establishing entitlement to relief under MCR 6.508(D). The motion to default appellee is DENIED.
